  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we were completely ignorant, not knowing at all what is going on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But somehow here and there, whether a postcard, or a mark, any kind of sign would come in telling us that these people that supposedly went out from the ghetto to labor camps and to better conditions did not reach to these camps.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Instead, they went to extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, when orders came in from the German authorities that they are looking, or they are asking for people to be sent out to work, fewer and fewer people would volunteer to these-- for these shipments.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they started to come in-- the Germans came in themselves and grab people for these-- for these purposes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Another occurrence was from time to time that the Germans applied pressure on the Judenrat, which is the self-government of the ghetto, which consisted of a-- of a leader by the name of Rumkowski with a mini cabinet, so to speak, which each member of this-- of this cabinet had a certain-- he was a head of a certain department.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the German-- the German authority ordered this Rumkowski, the leader of the ghetto, to supply Jews to be shipped out from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he, in a sense, was in a bind, because he requested the Jews to go voluntarily.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And since they refused, or the quota was not fulfilled according to the demand of the German authority, he was forced to use the Jewish police to take Jews from the houses and to fill in the amount of people that was needed.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Naturally, this created a resentment from the-- from the general Jewish population towards the establishment of this Judenrat, because he was-- he was accused of working together with the Germans against the Jewish population.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
